## Pipeline stages

| Stage | Agent(s) | Input | Output | Gate |
|-------|---------|-------|--------|------|
| **1. KB detection** | Rule (this file) | `knowledge-base/` vs `spec/kb-manifest.md` | New file list or "no changes" | New files → stage 2 |
| **2. Extraction** | Analyst | KB files | Proposed artefact updates | → stage 3 |
| **3. Validation** | UX agent | Analyst proposal + scope/KPIs | Validated proposal | UX agrees → stage 4 |
| **4. User review** | UX agent (presents) | Review document | User confirm/correct | Confirmed → stage 5 |
| **5. Spec write** | Analyst | Confirmed proposal | `spec/` updated, `kb-manifest` updated | → stage 6 |
| **6. Pocket subagents** | UX agent dynamically delegates to wireframe-figma, ia, design-system, use-case-scenario, content-design subagents (via Task tool) based on information at hand | Spec artefacts | Spec artefacts refined | → stage 7 |
| **7. Scoring** | UX agent | Refined artefacts | Confidence scores | ≥ 95% → stage 8; < 95% → stage 6 (max 3) |
| **8. Build** | UX agent (code plan) | Spec at 95%+ | Application code | Build succeeds → stage 9 |
| **9. Usability test** | Usability testing agent | Built code + spec | Assessment report | → stage 10 |
| **10. Reinforce** | Usability testing agent | Findings | `knowledge-base/auto-reinforcement.md` + agent learnings | → stage 1 (next cycle) |

